Fix libre office:

Go to TOOLS>OPTIONS>LIBREOFFICE>ACCESSIBILITY
in the section of "Options for high contrast appearance"
unchek all options

see: http://www.mediafire.com/view/?nzlfspuydo49n#v4jv7kndq2uawqe

#########################################

Go to TOOLS>OPTIONS>LIBREOFFICE>APAERANCE

Change the following colors:

    Document background: white
    Application background: gray 10%
    Text boundaries: gray 80%
    Font color: black (optional, only if you can't see the text )

see: http://www.mediafire.com/view/?nzlfspuydo49n#8llo9z71dwtcd2l

#########################################

Open the folder /usr/lib/libreoffice/program/shell

*Commands:

sudo su
nautilus /usr/lib/libreoffice/program/shell

see: http://www.mediafire.com/view/?nzlfspuydo49n#2wk1bsp3cfhca1p

rename o backup the following images:

* backing_left
* backing_right
* backing_space 

see: http://www.mediafire.com/view/?nzlfspuydo49n#j8fk1axfbo31mcc

copy the images from /DkGreen/workaround/libreoffice and paste in the folder /usr/lib/libreoffice/program/shell

finally this is how it looks: http://www.mediafire.com/view/?nzlfspuydo49n#6lclmip5n0uebkt

